	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Conrad shoots Mark.mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Conrad shoots Mark a warning look.
	Conrad: Keep your voice down.
	Mark: Relax, no one's listening. They're all too busy with the art.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Mark gestures.mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Mark gestures at the colorful displays surrounding them.
	Mark: Speaking of which - have you seen Mia's sculpture? The one that won regionals?
	Conrad: "The Reader"? I've heard it's the centerpiece of the exhibit.
	Mark: Let's check it out. Everyone's been talking about it.
