leave Celestine
leave Conrad
leave Mark
[background arg="res://Bg/courtyard.png" fade="0.5"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/They walk toward the center.mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
They walk toward the center of the courtyard.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/A crowd has gathered.mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
A crowd has gathered, but something feels wrong.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/The murmurs.mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
The murmurs aren't of admiration. They're of shock.
[wait time="0.5"]
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	join Celestine (half) left
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	Mark: What's going on? Why does everyone look so...
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/A student rushes past.mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	A student rushes past, face pale.
	Student: Someone destroyed Mia's sculpture! It's completely smashed!
	Celestine: What?
	Celestine pushes through the crowd, your detective instincts taking over.
	leave Celestine
	leave Mark
	[wait time="0.5"]
	[background arg="res://Bg/broken_sculpture.png" fade="0.0"]
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/The sculpture lies.mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	The sculpture lies shattered on the ground.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Clay fragments spread across.mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Clay fragments spread across the stone tiles. What was once art is now debris.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/The pedestal stands empty.mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	The pedestal stands empty, its plaque a bitter reminder of what was.
	[background arg="res://Bg/courtyard.png" fade="0.0"]
	join Celestine (half) left
	join Mia (half) right
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Mia kneels among the pieces.mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Mia kneels among the pieces, your hands hovering over the fragments as if afraid to touch them.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Tears stream silently.mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Tears stream silently down your face.
	Mia: Grandpa... I made this for you...
	Mia: You always said I could do anything. That my hands could create magic.
	Mia: Now it's gone. It's all gone.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Conrad approaches carefully.mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Celestine approaches carefully, keeping your voice gentle.
	Celestine: Mia?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/She looks up eyes red and hollow..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	She looks up, eyes red and hollow.
	Mia: Three months. Every night after school. Every weekend.
	Mia: My grandfather used to read to me under the mango tree in our backyard.
	Mia: He passed away last year. This was... this was my way of keeping him with me.
	Celestine: I'm so sorry. Truly.
	Mia: Who would do this? Why would anyone want to destroy something made from love?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Conrad notices something on the empty pedestal..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Celestine notices something on the empty pedestal.
	Celestine: Wait. What's that?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/A small note is tucked under the edge of the plaque..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	A small note is tucked under the edge of the plaque.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Conrad picks it up carefully reading aloud..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Celestine picks it up carefully, reading aloud.
	[signal arg="unlock_evidence cruel_note_c3"]
	join Mark (Mark_half) leftmost
	Mark: Celestine! What happened? Is Mia...
	Celestine: Someone destroyed her sculpture deliberately. And left this message.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Conrad shows Mark the note..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Celestine shows Mark the note.
	Mark: That's... that's cruel. Who writes something like that?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Conrad's expression hardens with determination..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	your expression hardens with determination.
	Celestine: Someone who feels overshadowed. Someone who wanted to hurt her specifically.
	Celestine: This wasn't random vandalism, Mark. This was personal.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/He turns to Mia his voice firm but kind..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	She turns to Mia, your voice firm but kind.
	Celestine: Mia, I've solved cases like this before. The exam sabotage. The missing outreach fund.
	Celestine: I promise you - I'm going to find out who did this and why.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Mia looks up a fragile hope breaking through her grief..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Mia looks up, a fragile hope breaking through your grief.
	Mia: You... you're the one who caught Greg? And found the missing money?
	Celestine: That's right. And whoever did this made a mistake.
	Celestine: They left evidence. Evidence always tells a story.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Conrad crouches near the debris examining the scene with practiced eyes..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Celestine crouches near the debris, examining the scene with practiced eyes.
	if {selected_subject} == "english":
		[signal arg="start_minigame dialogue_choice_cruel_note"]
	elif {selected_subject} == "math":
		Celestine: Let me analyze the evidence pattern systematically.
		Celestine: Three types of evidence: the note, the cloth, and the timing.
		Celestine: Each tells us something different about the culprit.
		[signal arg="start_minigame logic_grid_evidence_math"]
	elif {selected_subject} == "science":
		if {selected_character} == "celestine":
			Celestine: The vandalism involved different types of work and energy.
			Celestine: Pushing the sculpture, spray painting, running away...
			Celestine: I can analyze each action using physics principles!
		else:
			Conrad: The vandalism involved different types of work and energy.
			Conrad: Pushing the sculpture, spray painting, running away...
			Conrad: I can analyze each action using physics principles!
		[signal arg="start_minigame logic_grid_evidence_science"]
	Celestine: They left evidence.
	Celestine: The note itself is a clue. Handwritten. Emotional. Personal.
	Celestine: The sculpture was pushed, not kicked. Someone got close to it.
	Celestine: And... what's this?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/He picks up a small piece of cloth stained with various colors..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	She picks up a small piece of cloth, stained with various colors.
	Celestine: Paint-stained fabric. Someone dropped this.
	Mark: A clue already?
	Celestine: The beginning of one.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s1/Conrad straightens pocketing the cloth and the note carefully..mp3" volume=50 bus="Voice"]
	Celestine straightens, pocketing the cloth and the note carefully.
	Celestine: Mark, we have work to do.
	Mark: Just like old times.
	Celestine: Someone knows something. They always do.
	Celestine: Let's start with the art department. I want to know who had access to this courtyard last night.
	leave Celestine
	leave Mark
	leave Mia
